0partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20report%20to%20Congress%20Monday%2C%20the%20US%20intelligence%20community%20questioned%20%26quot%3BNetanyahu's%20viability%20as%20leader.%26quot%3B%20It%20predicted%20%26quot%3Blarge%20protests%20demanding%20his%20resignation%20and%20new%20elections%26quot%3B%20that%20it%20said%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20more%20moderate%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20likely%20that%20the%20Gaza%20conflict%20will%20have%20a%20generational%20impact%20on%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20underscoring%20US%20intelligence%20agencies'%20concerns%20about%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20devastation%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20Netanyahu%2C%20the%20country's%20longest-serving%20prime%20minister%2C%20made%20sure%20in%20his%20Sunday%20interview%20to%20argue%20that%20he's%20not%20leading%20his%20nation%20anywhere%20it%20doesn't%20wish%20to%20go.%20A%20recent%20poll%20by%20the%20Israel%20Democracy%20Institute%20found%2075%25%20of%20Jewish%20Israelis%20favor%20expanding%20military%20operations%20in%20Rafah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20spokeswoman%20Olivia%20Dalton%20said%20Monday%20that%20Biden's%20decades-long%20ties%20with%20the%20Israeli%20leader%20allow%20the%20US%20president%20%26quot%3Bto%20be%20direct%20and%20honest%20at%20a%20time%20where%20that's%20needed.%20But%20there's%20no%20change%20here%20in%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20two%20leaders'%20relationship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu%20says%20Israel%20will%20eventually%20invade%20Rafah%2C%20the%20southern%20Gaza%20city%2C%20where%20some%208%2C000%20Hamas%20fighters%2C%20its%20leaders%20and%20the%20remaining%20134%20Israeli%20hostages%20are%20thought%20to%20be%20ensconced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20doesn't%20want%20Israel%20to%20move%20forward%20out%20of%20fear%20that%20too%20many%20civilians%20will%20be%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20view%20is%20that%20no%20military%20operation%20should%20take%20place%20in%20Rafah%20if%20there%20is%20not%20a%20credible%20and%20implementable%20plan%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20needs%20of%20the%20more%20than%20a%20million%20civilians%20who%20are%20sheltering%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Dalton%2C%20the%20White%20House%20spokeswoman%2C%20said%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we've%20seen%20no%20such%20plan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20Forces%20Are%20Preparing%20a%20Push%20Into%20Rafah%20%7C%20More%20than%20one%20million%20people%20have%20sought%20refuge%20in%20the%20south%20Gaza%20city%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20Gantz%2C%20a%20popular%20opposition%20politician%2C%20met%20officials%20in%20Washington%20last%20week%2C%20his%20message%20was%20clear%3A%20The%20attack%20on%20Rafah%20must%20proceed%20eventually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tensions%20extend%20beyond%20the%20current%20fighting.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20believes%20that%20it's%20time%20to%20start%20planning%20for%20the%20day%20after%20the%20war%2C%20meaning%20a%20regional%20arrangement%20involving%20Saudi%20and%20Emirati%20aid%20for%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20to%20run%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20anathema%20to%20Netanyahu%20who%20says%20if%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20is%20the%20result%20of%20the%20October%207%20massacre%2C%20that%20rewards%20terror.%20Palestinians%2C%20he%20and%20his%20aides%20say%2C%20must%20learn%20the%20opposite%20-%20that%20violence%20will%20bring%20only%20harsh%20reprisal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20say%20something%20else%3A%20The%20more%20Biden%20tries%20to%20drive%20a%20wedge%20between%20the%20Israeli%20public%20and%20their%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20stronger%20he%20will%20make%20Netanyahu%20because%20voters%20don't%20appreciate%20such%20interference.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710231360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F42v9reng_joe-biden-netanyahu-reuters_650x400_18_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%