0being%20adopted%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20for%20appointments%20of%20the%20two%20empty%20spots%20in%20the%20EC%2C%20despite%20clear%20instructions%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20establishing%20a%20process%20that%20avoids%20the%20charge%20of%20partisan%2C%20executive-led%20appointments.%20He%20has%20termed%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20exclusion%20of%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Chard%20to%20fathom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Felection-commission-vacancies-moment-of-reckoning-9208292%2F%5C%22%3EHe%20writes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CJust%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20and%20three%20months%20after%20Parliament%20passed%20a%20law%20excluding%20the%20CJI%20from%20the%20committee%2C%20there%20are%20two%20vacancies%20in%20the%20ECI%20and%20the%20time%20to%20test%20the%20law%20and%20its%20spirit%20is%20here.%E2%80%9D%20Lavasa%20writes%20that%20excluding%20the%20CJI%2C%20whom%20he%20notes%2C%20has%20never%20really%20disagreed%20with%20the%20PM%20in%20other%20such%20selections%2C%20creates%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpredetermined%20bias%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20view.%E2%80%9D%20His%20exclusion%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20seem%20like%20an%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20a%20majority%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20consensus%20building.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELavasa%20has%20been%20explicit%20about%20failing%20to%20follow%20why%20the%20government%20initially%20equated%20the%20EC%20and%20the%20CEC%20with%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20but%20later%20displayed%20%E2%80%9Cmuddled%20thinking%E2%80%9D%20having%C2%A0%20apparently%20%E2%80%9Cstruck%20a%20bargain%E2%80%9D%20by%20restoring%20the%20equivalence%20of%20EC%2FCEC%20with%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20but%20then%20mysteriously%20reversing%20the%20parity%20in%20the%20removal%20process%20of%20the%20EC%20and%20CEC%2C%20to%20the%20original%20one%2C%20where%20