C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20was%20also%20attended%20by%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20top%20aides%2C%20director%20of%20the%20national%20security%20council%2C%20foreign%20policy%20advisor%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20terror%20attack%20on%20October%207%2C%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20had%20solely%20expressed%20solidarity%20with%20Israel.%20More%20than%201%2C200%20Israeli%20and%20foreign%20citizens%20were%20killed%20and%20250%20taken%20hostage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20military%20operation%2C%20which%20began%20with%20aerial%20bombing%2C%20followed%20by%20ground%20invasion%20of%20Gaza%20strip%2C%20has%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%20over%2030%2C000%20people%2C%20including%2025%2C000%20women%20and%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20deaths%20in%20Gaza%20became%20evident%2C%20India%20nuanced%20its%20position%20on%20the%20crisis%20by%20asserting%20that%20while%20terrorism%20was%20unacceptable%2C%20humanitarian%20aid%20had%20to%20be%20given%20at%20the%20earliest%20and%20reiterated%20traditional%20support%20for%20the%20two-state%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20December%202023%20resolution%20in%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20which%20called%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710212025000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12082209%2FGIZ-_OEWoAA9CVV.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnsa-ajit-doval-visits-israel-meets-benjamin-netanyahu%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Israeli%20account%20of%20the%20discussion%2C%20as%20shared%20on%20X%2C%20highlighted%20that%20the%20primary%20topic%20was%20the%20ongoing%20violence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnsa-ajit-doval-visits-israel-meets-benjamin-netan